---
export const prerender = true;
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import HomeCTA from '../components/home/HomeCTA.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="How It Works"
  description="Wondering what it actually looks like to work with N2M Technology? Here's how we assess, onboard, and manage your complete IT environment — from day one and beyond."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="hiw-hero">
    <div class="hiw-hero-dot-grid" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hiw-hero-inner">
      <span class="hiw-eyebrow">The N2M Approach</span>
      <h1 class="hiw-title">What it actually looks like to work with us.</h1>
      <p class="hiw-subtext">
        If you've been burned by an MSP before, you know the pattern: big promises,
        slow responses, and no clear ownership. N2M is built differently.
        Here's exactly what happens when you become a client.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Steps -->
  <section class="hiw-steps">
    <div class="hiw-steps-inner">

      <!-- Step 1 -->
      <div class="hiw-step reveal">
        <div class="hiw-step-marker">
          <span class="hiw-step-number">01</span>
        </div>
        <div class="hiw-step-content">
          <span class="hiw-step-label">Assessment</span>
          <h2 class="hiw-step-heading">We learn your environment before we touch it.</h2>
          <p class="hiw-step-body">
            Every new engagement starts with a thorough assessment of your current IT
            environment — what you have, how it's configured, where the gaps are, and
            what's at risk. We document everything: your network, your devices, your
            software, your physical infrastructure, and your existing vendor relationships.
          </p>
          <p class="hiw-step-body">
            Most clients tell us this is the first time anyone has ever done this for them.
            Many inherit environments from previous IT people that have never been fully
            documented. We fix that.
          </p>
          <p class="hiw-step-body">
            The output is a clear picture of where you stand and an honest conversation
            about what needs to change. No upsell pressure. No manufactured urgency.
            Just an accurate assessment you can make decisions from.
          </p>
          <div class="hiw-step-callout">
            <strong>What you get:</strong> A documented inventory of your IT environment and a frank assessment of your current risk posture.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hiw-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>

      <!-- Step 2 -->
      <div class="hiw-step reveal">
        <div class="hiw-step-marker">
          <span class="hiw-step-number">02</span>
        </div>
        <div class="hiw-step-content">
          <span class="hiw-step-label">Onboarding</span>
          <h2 class="hiw-step-heading">We take ownership. You hand off.</h2>
          <p class="hiw-step-body">
            Onboarding is where N2M transitions from assessing your environment to owning
            it. We deploy our monitoring and management tools across your infrastructure,
            establish your backup and recovery systems, configure security controls, and
            set the baseline we'll manage against from day one.
          </p>
          <p class="hiw-step-body">
            We handle the transition carefully — your team keeps working while we work
            around them. Downtime during onboarding should be zero or near-zero. If we
            anticipate any disruption, we plan it with you in advance and minimize the window.
          </p>
          <p class="hiw-step-body">
            By the end of onboarding, there's one number to call for every IT issue.
            Your team knows it. So does ours.
          </p>
          <div class="hiw-step-callout">
            <strong>What you get:</strong> Full monitoring coverage deployed, security baseline configured, your team oriented to working with us, and a clear single point of contact.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hiw-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>

      <!-- Step 3 -->
      <div class="hiw-step reveal">
        <div class="hiw-step-marker">
          <span class="hiw-step-number">03</span>
        </div>
        <div class="hiw-step-content">
          <span class="hiw-step-label">Ongoing Management</span>
          <h2 class="hiw-step-heading">We manage. You don't have to think about it.</h2>
          <p class="hiw-step-body">
            This is the model in practice: N2M monitors your environment continuously,
            handles maintenance and patching on schedule, responds to issues before they
            become outages, and manages your vendors so you don't have to.
          </p>
          <p class="hiw-step-body">
            When your team has a problem, they call or message us and get a qualified
            engineer — not a routing script. Response times are fast because we already
            know your environment. Most issues are resolved in the same interaction.
          </p>
          <p class="hiw-step-body">
            And because we're proactive — not reactive — most issues don't reach your
            team at all. We catch them in monitoring before they surface.
          </p>
          <div class="hiw-step-callout">
            <strong>What you get:</strong> 24/7 monitoring, fast response, proactive maintenance, and a managed environment that gets more stable over time — not less.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hiw-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>

      <!-- Step 4 -->
      <div class="hiw-step reveal">
        <div class="hiw-step-marker">
          <span class="hiw-step-number">04</span>
        </div>
        <div class="hiw-step-content">
          <span class="hiw-step-label">Partnership & Growth</span>
          <h2 class="hiw-step-heading">We grow with your business.</h2>
          <p class="hiw-step-body">
            A good IT partner doesn't just maintain the status quo — they help you think
            about what comes next. As your business grows, your IT environment should
            scale with it. N2M reviews your infrastructure regularly and brings
            recommendations to you before you have to ask.
          </p>
          <p class="hiw-step-body">
            Whether that means expanding your network for a new location, deploying AI
            automation to eliminate a manual process, or upgrading your physical security
            when you add a facility — we're already thinking about it.
          </p>
          <p class="hiw-step-body">
            The relationship is designed to get more valuable over time. We know your
            business. We know your infrastructure. We're invested in both.
          </p>
          <div class="hiw-step-callout">
            <strong>What you get:</strong> A partner who knows your environment and brings you ideas — not just a team that responds to problems.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Reassurance section -->
  <section class="hiw-reassurance">
    <div class="hiw-reassurance-inner">
      <div class="hiw-reassurance-grid">
        <div class="hiw-reassurance-card reveal reveal-delay-1">
          <div class="hiw-reassurance-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M22 16.92v3a2 2 0 0 1-2.18 2 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-8.63-3.07A19.5 19.5 0 0 1 4.99 12 19.79 19.79 0 0 1 1.95 3.25a2 2 0 0 1 1.99-2.18h3a2 2 0 0 1 2 1.72c.127.96.361 1.903.7 2.81a2 2 0 0 1-.45 2.11L8.09 8.91a16 16 0 0 0 5.99 5.99l1.27-1.27a2 2 0 0 1 2.11-.45c.907.339 1.85.573 2.81.7A2 2 0 0 1 22 16.92z"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="hiw-reassurance-heading">One number. Always answered.</h3>
          <p class="hiw-reassurance-text">You call one number and reach someone who knows your environment. Not a routing queue. Not a form to fill out.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hiw-reassurance-card reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="hiw-reassurance-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="hiw-reassurance-heading">No finger-pointing.</h3>
          <p class="hiw-reassurance-text">When something goes wrong, the answer is never "that's someone else's problem." N2M owns your environment. We own the outcome.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hiw-reassurance-card reveal reveal-delay-3">
          <div class="hiw-reassurance-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
              <polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="hiw-reassurance-heading">Proactive, not reactive.</h3>
          <p class="hiw-reassurance-text">We catch most issues before they reach you. The goal isn't fast response times — it's fewer problems in the first place.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <HomeCTA />
</PageLayout>

<style>
  /* Hero */
  .hiw-hero {
    background: var(--color-navy);
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem 4.5rem;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .hiw-hero-dot-grid {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-image: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(0, 157, 219, 0.1) 1px, transparent 1px);
    background-size: 28px 28px;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .hiw-hero-inner {
    position: relative;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .hiw-eyebrow {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
  }

  .hiw-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-hero);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: white;
    line-height: 1.12;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .hiw-subtext {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.65);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 56ch;
  }

  /* Steps */
  .hiw-steps {
    padding: var(--section-padding) 1.5rem;
    background: var(--color-white);
  }

  .hiw-steps-inner {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .hiw-step {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 80px 1fr;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .hiw-step-marker {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    padding-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .hiw-step-number {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    opacity: 0.25;
  }

  .hiw-step-label {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .hiw-step-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.625rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .hiw-step-body {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .hiw-step-callout {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.125rem 1.375rem;
    background: #f0f7fb;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .hiw-step-callout strong {
    color: var(--color-navy);
  }

  .hiw-divider {
    width: 1px;
    height: 3rem;
    background: var(--color-border);
    margin: 3rem 0 3rem 39px;
  }

  /* Reassurance */
  .hiw-reassurance {
    background: var(--color-navy);
    padding: var(--section-padding) 1.5rem;
  }

  .hiw-reassurance-inner {
    max-width: 1280px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .hiw-reassurance-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .hiw-reassurance-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .hiw-reassurance-icon {
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    background: rgba(0, 157, 219, 0.15);
    border-radius: 10px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .hiw-reassurance-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: white;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .hiw-reassurance-text {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hiw-step {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .hiw-step-marker {
      flex-direction: row;
      gap: 0.75rem;
      align-items: center;
      padding-top: 0;
    }

    .hiw-step-number {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }

    .hiw-divider {
      margin: 2rem 0;
    }

    .hiw-reassurance-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2.5rem;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hiw-reassurance-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
